data.title: Windows Server 2003 build 3790.1232
data.meta_description: An open encyclopedia of software history
data.text:
Not to be confused with Windows Server 2008 build 3790.1232.

5.2.3790.1232.040817Build of Windows Server 2003OS familyWindows NTVersion number5.2Build number3790Build revision1232Architecturex86Compiled onExpiration dateTimebomb (+360 days)SKUsWeb Server

Windows Server 2003 build 3790.1232 is a beta build of Windows Server 2003 Service Pack 1. A disc containing this build was featured in a picture of multiple burn lab discs shared by ReflectiaX in 2018.

This is technically the base build for post-reset Windows Vista, as the new winmain build lab branched off the Windows Server 2003 codebase when it was the latest compiled build. The first winmain build, also numbered 3790.1232, is merely a recompile of this build from the new lab.
